My church is called Saint Pancras church. It is a nice church and I go to Sunday school with my brother while my mum and dad go to church.
The church is very old and was built in the 16th century and then rebuilt in the 18th century. One year ago it had an extention built and we call it the lounge. Here are some of the things that happen at our church: Scouts,Brownies,Guides, a playschool, a coffee bar which is for teenagers, which is a youth club also. My mummy helps to run it.
The church is for anyone who wants to come along.We go to church because we believe in Jesus and my family are Christians. {Scott Gifford (age 8)}
